        "text": "\"Whatever fragmentation is going on; formation, completion, is also going on. Whatever formation is going on; destruction is also going on.\"\n\nfrom Zhuangzi, Inner Chapter II\n\nErich Von Stroheim is the soul of Edmond T. Greville's tense creation of Paris in the grim days leading up to WWII. His characterization of Mr. Hoffman, an Austrian whose face had been partially torn-off in WWI, sets the metaphorical bellwether of emotions toward war and civilization itself in Greville's 1940 film Menaces. Within a small Parisienne hotel we watch a cross-section of French and Eastern European refugee guests attempting to deal with their individual fears for loved ones, themselves, their countrymen, yet attempting to bolster plans and dreams for a more benign future.â€¦"
